sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT user_id)
FROM issue_assignees
WHERE is_active = 1;

SELECT DISTINCT systems.system_id, systems.system_name
FROM systems
INNER JOIN api_keys ON systems.system_id = api_keys.system_id;

external_knowledge:
- 'Explorers' and 'wanderers' metaphorically refer to users who have posted comments;
- 'Pathways in the vast forest of discussion' symbolically represents comments made on issues;
- The average number of pathways traversed by wanderers represents the average number of comments made per user.

sql:
SELECT user_id, COUNT(*)
FROM issue_comments
GROUP BY user_id;

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT system_id)
FROM systems
WHERE system_id > 5 AND status = 'active';
